    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-04-12T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-04-12T12:00:00-05:00" n="500"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d500">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">251.11 Insull, Samuel/537: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Istanbul</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-04-12T19:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 12, 1934—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 12—5:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>23. Insull, accompanied by Colonel Crane and Berry, in custody Turkish officials
                    departed 7 p.m. by steamer for Izmir, expecting to transfer to <hi rend="italic"
                        >Exilona</hi> Friday evening.<note n="49" xml:id="d500fn49">April 13.</note>
                    Please have Berry relieved of responsibility at quarantine New York informing
                    him regarding identifying documents of relieving officer.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
